# Domo
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** cloud-based business intelligence / data analytics
**Website:** https://www.domo.com

## Overview
Domo is a cloud-native business intelligence (BI) and data integration platform that enables organizations to unify, visualize, and act on their data in real time. The platform connects to hundreds of data sources—databases, spreadsheets, SaaS applications—and provides dashboards, embedded analytics, and low-code app-building tools. Domo’s value proposition is to replace fragmented BI stacks with a single, mobile-first system that puts actionable insights into the hands of non-technical users.

Founded in 2010, Domo went public on the Nasdaq in 2018 (ticker: DOMO). The company serves midsize to large enterprises across industries including retail, financial services, healthcare, and manufacturing. It competes with Tableau, Power BI, and Looker but differentiates through its data pipeline automation, connector ecosystem, and emphasis on executive-friendly dashboards.

## Utah connection
Domo is headquartered in American Fork, Utah, and is a flagship company of the Silicon Slopes tech hub. Its founders drew on Utah’s deep pool of data and engineering talent, and the company remains one of the state’s largest publicly traded cloud software firms. Domo has contributed to Utah’s reputation as a center for enterprise SaaS and data analytics innovation, and it actively participates in local tech events and workforce development initiatives.

